ml.alternet.security.auth.formats

Class ModularCryptFormat

  • java.lang.Object
    • ml.alternet.security.auth.formats.CryptFormatBase
      • ml.alternet.security.auth.formats.ModularCryptFormat
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CryptFormat, DiscoverableCryptFormat

    @Singleton
public class ModularCryptFormat
extends CryptFormatBase
implements CryptFormat
    The Modular Crypt Format is an ad-hoc standard used in popular linux-based systems. Format : $[scheme]$[salt]$[crypt]
    IDMethod
    1MD5
    2aBlowfish
    5SHA-256
    6SHA-512

    Examples :

    • Apache MD5 crypt format : 
      $apr1$jgwedrkq$jzeetEHMGal5H0SUFDMEl1
    • Crypt MD5 : 
      $1$3iuE5z/b$JHyXMzQOIq3cl6WlEMoZC.
    Author:
    Philippe Poulard
    See Also:
    ModularCryptFormat.Hashers
